snippet: A three-day discussion of issues that ended Friday did not result in concrete decisions on pressing matters facing lawmakers.
abstract: House Republicans end three-day retreat united in their division; they remain unable to coalesce around their approach on overhauling the immigration laws, increasing the nation’s borrowing limit, providing an alternative to the Affordable Care Act or whether to press forward with tax code rewrite.
lead_paragraph: A three-day discussion of issues that ended Friday did not result in concrete decisions on pressing matters facing lawmakers.
